<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="220" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,653,1114,1136]" box="[151,653,1114,1136]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">
Type species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1894" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1894" box="[294,653,1114,1136]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Chrosiothes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvaticus">
<emphasis box="[294,517,1114,1136]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Chrosiothes silvaticus</emphasis>
Simon, 1894
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1181,1926]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1661822631" country="Brazil" county="Oriental Region" location="Neotropical Region" municipality="Neartic Region" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" specimenCount="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,510,1181,1206]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Composition and distribution.</emphasis>
Twentyseven species, including the six new species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1894" box="[1126,1260,1181,1206]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Chrosiothes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1126,1260,1181,1206]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Chrosiothes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described here. The genus has eleven species unique to the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:735587E6FFB3D22AFF1BFBE0B07021D5:FE23602BFFB3D22AFD00FB35B1692289" box="[652,876,1217,1242]" country="Brazil" county="Oriental Region" municipality="Neartic Region" name="Neotropical Region" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Neotropical Region</location>
, nine species unique to the 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1193,1368,1217,1242]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Neartic Region</collectingMunicipality>
, three species unique to the 
<collectingCounty box="[390,573,1253,1278]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Oriental Region</collectingCounty>
, and four species shared between the Neotropical and Neartic Regions. In the present study was expanded the distribution of the genus in 
<collectingCountry box="[821,889,1289,1314]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[905,989,1289,1314]" captionStart="FIGURE 29" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1499,1521]" captionTargetBox="[324,1246,194,1464]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[324,1247,193,1464]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 29. Distribution of current and new records of the genus Chrosiothes in Brazil." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1002478/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="220" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1181,1926]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1325,1350]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1894" box="[331,465,1325,1350]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Chrosiothes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[331,465,1325,1350]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Chrosiothes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species differ from the other genus of the 
<taxonomicName box="[967,1109,1325,1350]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Spintharinae">Spintharinae</taxonomicName>
by the presence of an outer lateral tubercle on the patellae I–V, conspicuous lateral tubercle in 
<emphasis box="[913,1047,1361,1386]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Chrosiohtes</emphasis>
and inconspicuous in other genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Duran-Barron" box="[158,454,1397,1422]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" refString="Duran-Barron, C. G., Rosas, M. V. &amp; Contreras-Ramos, A. (2013) Phylogenetic relationships of the comb-footed spider subfamily Spintharinae (Araneae, Araneoidea, Theridiidae), with generic diagnoses and a key to the genera. Zootaxa, 3666 (2), 171 - 193. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3666.2.4" type="journal article" year="2013">
Durán-Barrón 
<emphasis box="[324,373,1397,1422]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">et al</emphasis>
., 2013
</bibRefCitation>
) and cymbium of the male palp is triangular-shape (
<bibRefCitation author="Duran-Barron" box="[1041,1339,1397,1422]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" refString="Duran-Barron, C. G., Rosas, M. V. &amp; Contreras-Ramos, A. (2013) Phylogenetic relationships of the comb-footed spider subfamily Spintharinae (Araneae, Araneoidea, Theridiidae), with generic diagnoses and a key to the genera. Zootaxa, 3666 (2), 171 - 193. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3666.2.4" type="journal article" year="2013">
Durán-Barrón 
<emphasis box="[1208,1256,1397,1422]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">et al</emphasis>
., 2013
</bibRefCitation>
), oval in other spintharines genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Duran-Barron" box="[435,730,1433,1458]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" refString="Duran-Barron, C. G., Rosas, M. V. &amp; Contreras-Ramos, A. (2013) Phylogenetic relationships of the comb-footed spider subfamily Spintharinae (Araneae, Araneoidea, Theridiidae), with generic diagnoses and a key to the genera. Zootaxa, 3666 (2), 171 - 193. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3666.2.4" type="journal article" year="2013">
Durán-Barrón 
<emphasis box="[600,648,1433,1458]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">et al</emphasis>
., 2013
</bibRefCitation>
). Differ from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cambridge" authorityYear="1894" box="[883,995,1434,1457]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Stemmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[883,995,1434,1457]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Stemmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the spinneret sclerotized ring absent (Agnarsson, 2004; 
<bibRefCitation author="Duran-Barron" box="[363,653,1469,1494]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" refString="Duran-Barron, C. G., Rosas, M. V. &amp; Contreras-Ramos, A. (2013) Phylogenetic relationships of the comb-footed spider subfamily Spintharinae (Araneae, Araneoidea, Theridiidae), with generic diagnoses and a key to the genera. Zootaxa, 3666 (2), 171 - 193. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3666.2.4" type="journal article" year="2013">
Durán-Barron 
<emphasis box="[526,574,1469,1494]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">et al</emphasis>
., 2013
</bibRefCitation>
) and by the PME far from laterals, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cambridge" authorityYear="1894" box="[1073,1186,1470,1493]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Stemmops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1073,1186,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Stemmops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
PME close to laterals; from 
<taxonomicName box="[214,337,1505,1530]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Thwaitesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[214,337,1505,1530]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Thwaitesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the alveolar cavity in the male cymbium non sclerotized (Agnarsson, 2004; 
<bibRefCitation author="Duran-Barron" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" refString="Duran-Barron, C. G., Rosas, M. V. &amp; Contreras-Ramos, A. (2013) Phylogenetic relationships of the comb-footed spider subfamily Spintharinae (Araneae, Araneoidea, Theridiidae), with generic diagnoses and a key to the genera. Zootaxa, 3666 (2), 171 - 193. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3666.2.4" type="journal article" year="2013">
Durán-Barrón 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">et al</emphasis>
., 2013
</bibRefCitation>
) and by the silvery pigment in abdominal dorsum absent; from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marques, Buckup &amp; Lopes Rodrigues" authorityYear="2011" box="[975,1100,1542,1565]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Neopisinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[975,1100,1542,1565]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Neopisinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of conductor, in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marques, Buckup &amp; Lopes Rodrigues" authorityYear="2011" box="[151,276,1578,1601]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Neopisinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,276,1578,1601]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Neopisinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the male palp with an enormous trifid conductor with two pointed structures and the third one apically bifurcated (
<bibRefCitation author="Marques" box="[283,524,1613,1638]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" refString="Marques, M. A. L., Buckup, E. H. &amp; Rodrigues, E. N. L. (2011) Novo genero neotropical de Spintharinae (Araneae, Theridiidae). Iheringia, Serie Zoologia, 101 (4), 372 - 381. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0073 - 47212011000300011" type="journal article" year="2011">
Marques 
<emphasis box="[395,456,1613,1638]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
, figs. 1, 2); from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1932" box="[742,819,1613,1638]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Janula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[742,819,1613,1638]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Janula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the carapace without two large conical tubercles bearing the AME (
<emphasis box="[363,425,1650,1673]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">sensu</emphasis>
Yoshida &amp; Koh 2011, figs. 28–30, 38–40) from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hentz" authorityYear="1850" box="[974,1095,1649,1674]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Spintharus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[974,1095,1649,1674]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Spintharus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of cymbial hood (
<bibRefCitation author="Duran-Barron" box="[158,458,1685,1710]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" refString="Duran-Barron, C. G., Rosas, M. V. &amp; Contreras-Ramos, A. (2013) Phylogenetic relationships of the comb-footed spider subfamily Spintharinae (Araneae, Araneoidea, Theridiidae), with generic diagnoses and a key to the genera. Zootaxa, 3666 (2), 171 - 193. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3666.2.4" type="journal article" year="2013">
Durán-Barrón 
<emphasis box="[325,374,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">et al</emphasis>
., 2013
</bibRefCitation>
); and differ from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walckenaer, in Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[660,756,1686,1709]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Episinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[660,756,1686,1709]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Episinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the opisthosoma is inclined in relation to the location of the pedicel (
<bibRefCitation author="Duran-Barron" box="[286,581,1721,1746]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" refString="Duran-Barron, C. G., Rosas, M. V. &amp; Contreras-Ramos, A. (2013) Phylogenetic relationships of the comb-footed spider subfamily Spintharinae (Araneae, Araneoidea, Theridiidae), with generic diagnoses and a key to the genera. Zootaxa, 3666 (2), 171 - 193. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3666.2.4" type="journal article" year="2013">
Durán-Barrón 
<emphasis box="[452,501,1721,1746]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">et al</emphasis>
., 2013
</bibRefCitation>
), in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walckenaer, in Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[628,725,1722,1745]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Episinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[628,725,1722,1745]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Episinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is straight. Of the species that do not occur in the Neotropical Region, differ from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wunderlich" authorityYear="2008" box="[386,548,1758,1781]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Pycnoepisinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[386,548,1758,1781]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Pycnoepisinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the stridulatory organ between legs I and II (
<bibRefCitation author="Wunderlich" box="[1119,1428,1757,1782]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" refString="Wunderlich, J. (2008) On extant and fossil (Eocene) European comb-footed spiders (Araneae: Theridiidae), with notes on their subfamilies, and with descriptions of new taxa. Beitrage zur Araneologie, 5, 140 - 859." type="journal article" year="2008">Wunderlich 2008, fig. 384</bibRefCitation>
) absent; from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1906" box="[300,385,1794,1817]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Moneta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[300,385,1794,1817]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Moneta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of eyes, in dorsal view, in two parallel rows in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1906" box="[1116,1202,1794,1817]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Moneta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1116,1202,1794,1817]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Moneta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Saaristo" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" refString="Saaristo, M. I. (2006) Theridiid or cobweb spiders of the granitic Seychelles islands (Araneae, Theridiidae). Phelsuma, 14, 49 - 89." type="journal article" year="2006">Saaristo 2006, figs. 45–47</bibRefCitation>
); and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yoshida &amp; Koh" authorityYear="2011" box="[371,519,1830,1853]" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Brunepisinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[371,519,1830,1853]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Brunepisinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of rounded tubercles projecting anteriorly from the carapace (Yoshida &amp; Koh 2011, see figs. 57, 58) and by the absence of stridulating organ in male first coxae and second femora (Yoshida &amp; Koh 2011, see fig. 61).
</paragraph>
